body.description: SwissGear Sion Softside Expandable Check-In Spinner Luggage gives you an ample amount of packing space when needed. This rolling suitcase features a locking push/pull handle system and four 360-degree multi-directional spinner wheels for convenient portability. It is made from a durable, scuff-resistant polyester fabric and its interior is fully lined. This check-in suitcase features adjustable luggage tie-down straps for securing garments in place, a removable zippered wet bag, a large mesh lid pocket, and a packing pocket for holding small items and accessories. It also includes two front panel pockets, a built-in ID tag, and padded top and side handles. At SwissGear, we continue to ensure whatever you need travels easily, safely, and stylishly with you. Great for a family trip or business travel.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars SwissGear Sion Luggage: A Traveler's Delight
reviews.reviewText: I recently invested in the SwissGear Sion Softside Expandable Luggage in the stunning burgundy color, and it's been a game-changer for my travels. The 25-inch size is perfect for medium-length trips, offering ample space without being too cumbersome.What stands out is the luggage's durability. The fabric feels robust and has held up well against the rigors of travel. The expandable feature is a lifesaver, especially when I've needed that extra bit of space for souvenirs or additional items.The wheels glide smoothly, making navigating through busy airports a breeze. Another aspect I appreciate is the number of compartments and pockets, which helps in organizing my belongings effectively.I'm also a fan of the color – the burgundy is rich and easily stands out on the baggage carousel, making it quick to spot.Overall, the SwissGear Sion Softside Expandable Luggage strikes a great balance between style, functionality, and durability. It's a solid choice for anyone looking for reliable luggage for their travel needs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Just got this today. It was out of stock for a couple weeks. Love the color. More vibrant than the photos. Seems like good quality material. Like the inside pockets. I went back to soft side after a two week trip to Europe using hard side bag with many hotels. Soft is much easier to open with less space taken up. I can fit packing cubes in easily. Doesn’t seem as bulky as hard side to get around in airports etc. Can’t wait to try it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great carry on suitcase, great deal!
reviews.reviewText: After searching Amazon & Macy’s apps for 2 weeks looking for a carry on for my son, I checked out countless hard side & soft side options & poured over reviews. I finally settled on this soft sided carry on. Amazon buyers had posted some useful videos & the reviews for this bag were consistently awesome. I wanted something with good quality spinner wheels & a telescoping handle that was sturdy. The bag needed to be affordable and have nice features inside & out. This carry on checked all of those boxes! Very impressed with the look & quality of this bag, both inside & out. Smooth zips with high quality zipper pulls, 2 handy & spacious exterior pockets for easy access to travel essentials (this is why I chose soft side over hard side!) a separate expansion zipper for more packing space for clothing, and I love that it has sturdy handles on three sides to easily grab this bag from any angle. One side has nice “feet” if you want to set the bag down horizontally. The telescoping handle works smoothly and locks into place. There’s two different height choices for this handle. One feature it has that nobody mentioned is that the zippers have little holes you can align and you can then use your own suitcase padlock on the bag if needed. The interior is spacious, nicely lined and there’s an attached mesh zipper pocket on one of the long sides, and also a detachable zip bag they call a wet bag, so stuff your wet swimsuit inside if need be or use it for cosmetics or whatever. Not sure if it’s TSA friendly because it’s clear, but not exactly see through. The spinner wheels glide as smooth as silk across my wood floors here at home & it has excellent maneuverability. A nice dark blue, soft materiel. It’s a great looking bag! I got a really outstanding deal on this when I checked out the list of these bags available at a lower price, shipped from the Amazon warehouse. I chose an option that stated it would be “Used, in like new condition” that was listed $30 cheaper than new. It came in pristine packaging, no damage whatsoever to the box that held the suitcase and still taped up with “Swiss Gear” packaging tape. The suitcase & handles were still wrapped in plastic, tags were intact, and all of the pockets on the suitcase still were stuffed with the packaging tissue paper! This was an awesome score for under $100 and I’m sure this thing will last a very long time! Look no further, this is the perfect carry on bag. I’m sure Swiss Gear’s matching larger size bags are just as awesome, too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good amount of space, not high end quality
reviews.reviewText: I like this brand and have the large version of this suitcase and like it for my checked luggage. So I tried the carry on but was comparing it to another more expensive brand. I really wanted to like this one because it has a bit more interior space. I like the large outside pocket, which I would use more than the two small ones a lot of styles have on the outside. But this suitcase is several pounds heavier and does not maneuver as nicely as an 8-wheel style. The handle feels loose/flimsy when extended and the button that retracts it sticks up higher than the rest of the handle so you can easily press it by accident. I ended up keeping the more expensive one once I got a taste for nicer quality, even though that one is a tad smaller inside. I will say this one has good reinforcement on the bottom corners too.

Over a dozen trips so far. Still going strong with all the zippers and wheels intact.Got it "used" from the Warehouse Deals but received what seemed to be a brand new unit. Cheap, sturdy, and looks just as good as the $$$ ones 😎
